Uzbek and Kara-Kalpak

                            apertium-uzb-kaa
===============================================================================

This is an Apertium language pair for translating between Uzbek and
Kara-Kalpak. What you can use this language package for:

* Translating between Uzbek and Kara-Kalpak
* Morphological analysis of Uzbek and Kara-Kalpak
* Part-of-speech tagging of Uzbek and Kara-Kalpak

For information on the latter two points, see subheading "For more
information" below

Requirements
===============================================================================

You will need the following software installed:

* lttoolbox (>= 3.3.0)
* apertium (>= 3.3.0)
* vislcg3 (>= 0.9.9.10297)
* hfst (>= 3.8.2)
* apertium-uzb
* apertium-kaa

If this does not make any sense, we recommend you look at: www.apertium.org

Compiling
===============================================================================

Given the requirements being installed, you should be able to just run:

$ ./configure
$ make
# make install

You can use ./autogen.sh instead of ./configure you're compiling from
SVN. If you installed any prerequisite language packages using a --prefix
to ./configure, make sure to give the same --prefix to ./configure here.

Testing
===============================================================================

If you are in the source directory after running make, the following
commands should work:

$  echo "TODO test sentence 1" | apertium -d . uzb-kaa
TODO test translated sentence 1

$ echo "TODO test sentence 2" | apertium -d . kaa-uzb
TODO test translated sentence 2

After installing somewhere in $PATH, you should be able to do e.g.

$  echo "TODO test sentence 1" | apertium uzb-kaa
TODO test translated sentence 1

Files and data
===============================================================================

* apertium-uzb-kaa.uzb-kaa.dix  - Bilingual dictionary
* apertium-uzb-kaa.uzb-kaa.t1x  - Chunking rules for translating into Uzbek
* apertium-uzb-kaa.kaa-uzb.t1x  - Chunking rules for translating into Kara-Kalpak
* apertium-uzb-kaa.uzb-kaa.t2x  - Interchunk rules for translating into Uzbek
* apertium-uzb-kaa.kaa-uzb.t2x  - Interchunk rules for translating into Kara-Kalpak
* apertium-uzb-kaa.uzb-kaa.t3x  - Postchunk rules for translating into Uzbek
* apertium-uzb-kaa.kaa-uzb.t3x  - Postchunk rules for translating into Kara-Kalpak
* apertium-uzb-kaa.uzb-kaa.lrx  - Lexical selection rules for translating into Uzbek
* apertium-uzb-kaa.kaa-uzb.lrx  - Lexical selection rules for translating into Kara-Kalpak
* modes.xml                     - Translation modes

For more information
===============================================================================

